	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In short:
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">pin 45 &#40;audio in to cart from famicom&#41; -&gt; 10k resitor -&gt; pin 46 &#40;audio out of cart to famicom output&#41;<br />powerpak audio pin &#40;72 pin connector 'exp pin 6'&#41; -&gt; &#40;optional 10uf ceramic capacitor, see below&#41; -&gt; pin 46<br /></div>
<br />
<br />If you end up with DC clicking/saturation problems with sound when low notes are played on the powerpak, place a 10uf capacitor between the powerpak pin and pin 46
<br />
<br />LN

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


